fields.title: Yearly Bundle - Gold
fields.description: 12 month fully comprehensive membership - includes full travel expenses for club shows and sparring, 5 x family tickets for all events, and full set of club apparel and boxing gear. Great for young prospects!

fields.question: Is the club open to all levels?
fields.answer: Yes, it's completely open. We have always had a mix of complete novice boxers, and experienced amateur boxers. But you will expected to work hard to bring up your level, and compete to gain experience. This is an amateur boxing academy. It's not suitable for people who want to train boxing only for fitness.

fields.question: Is the club open to all sexes?
fields.answer: Yes absolutely. We have male and female members at the club, of all levels and weights. You will be matched by your sex, level and weight when it comes to sparring. But otherwise we all train together, and support each other at fights.

fields.question: How often a week is training?
fields.answer: Training is every Monday, Thursday and Sunday. On the weekdays, we train from 7pm to 9pm. But on Sunday, we train from 11am - 1pm. Boxers must arrive 15 minutes before training, and train for the full duration.

fields.question: What do we need to bring to training?
fields.answer: You must bring a boxing top, boxing shorts, a mouthguard, headguard, groin shield, handwraps and gloves; 16oz is mandatory for sparring and 12oz is optional for the bags. You can get most of these items in our ecommerce shop on this website.

fields.question: Do we have to spar in training?
fields.answer: Yes, every training session includes sparring in the ring. Sparring is mandatory. It is also strictly refereed by a coach to ensure the safety of both fighters at all times.And you will not be paired with someone who is more experienced, or in a higher weight category.

fields.question: How much is membership?
fields.answer: You can see all of our membership options and categories in our ecommerce store. Membership is separated into yearly, quarterly and monthly categories, and gold and silver levels. We have capacity for 35 members in any season, so spots are limited!

fields.question: How much is boxing gear?
fields.answer: This question depends on where you shop. But you'll find boxing gear in our ecommerce shop on this website which is priced at benchmark level. We'd ask you to support the club by buying from us. You can find cheaper gear elsewhere, but we guarantee the quality of our gear, and it will help support our facilities and events.
